# Review-governance recommendation, not a verified enforcement mechanism.
#
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the listed owner(s) on any PR that
# touches a matching path. That much is guaranteed by this file alone.
# Whether it actually *blocks* merging without that review depends on
# this repository's branch protection settings ("Require review from
# Code Owners") -- a setting this file cannot configure or verify, and
# which has not been confirmed as enabled. Treat the paths below as
# "must get a human's attention," not as a proven hard gate, until
# someone with repository admin access confirms the branch protection
# setting is on.
#
# Owner is a placeholder ("@OWNER") -- replace with the real GitHub
# username/team before this offers any actual auto-request behavior.

# The CI workflow, and specifically its flake8 regression-gate baseline
# (FLAKE8_BASELINE), must not be silently raised in the same PR that
# introduces the violations it's meant to catch.
/.github/workflows/ci.yml   @OWNER

# The authoritative status document should not drift from what the code
# actually verifies.
/docs/architecture/current-status.md   @OWNER
